        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 8:03AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 803 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hanceville, or near Blountsville, moving east at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
McLarty, Nectar, Easley, Chamblees Mill, Snead, Cleveland, Rosa,
Fairview, Bangor, Oneonta, Fowler Spring, Strawberry, Hendrix,
Brooksville, Blountsville, Susan Moore, Altoona, and Walnut Grove.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon CDT for
central and northeastern Alabama.</instruction>
